{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018nSD1tnZnk1PBoiosdiN8k","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Code Review Summary for Story 15-3: Template Migration -- Static Files**\n\n**Verdict: PASS -- no HIGH or MEDIUM issues found.**\n\nThe implementation is clean and well-structured:\n\n- `renderTemplate()` and `renderTemplateFile()` in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/templates.ts` are correct, well-tested, and handle edge cases (empty vars, unmatched placeholders, multiple occurrences).\n- All migrated templates (`dockerfiles/`, `compose/`, `prompts/`, `docs/`) match their former TypeScript counterparts.\n- Stack providers (`nodejs.ts`, `python.ts`, `rust.ts`) correctly use `renderTemplateFile()` for Dockerfile generation.\n- `docker-compose.ts`, `otel-config.ts`, `readme.ts`, and `ralph-prompt.ts` all correctly delegate to `renderTemplateFile()`.\n- `verify-prompt.ts` and `showboat-template.ts` were intentionally not migrated (complex logic that doesn't reduce to simple `{{VAR}}` interpolation). Correct decision.\n- `package.json` `files` field includes all new template directories for npm distribution.\n- 31 migration-specific tests in `template-migration.test.ts` cover AC1 (directory structure), AC2 (TypeScript generators replaced), and AC3 (output equivalence).\n- All 3777 tests pass. Coverage at 97.1%. All 156 files above 80% per-file floor.\n- Build succeeds.\n\nStory status updated from `review` to `verifying`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:** None.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- `dockerComposeTemplate(_config: DockerComposeConfig)` ignores the `shared` boolean parameter entirely. The function always returns `victoria.yml`. Pre-existing tech debt, not introduced by this story.\n- `otelCollectorConfigWithCors()` injects CORS via regex string manipulation on the YAML output rather than YAML-level manipulation. Fragile if indentation changes in the base template file. Pre-existing, not introduced by this story.\n- Ralph prompt template uses camelCase `{{projectDir}}`, `{{sprintStatusPath}}` while all other templates use `{{SCREAMING_SNAKE}}` convention. Inconsistent but functional since `\\w+` matches both. Introduced by this story but LOW impact.\n- `bmad-patches.ts` uses its own `__dirname`-based path resolution instead of the centralized `getPackageRoot()` from `templates.ts`. Pre-existing.\n\n**Coverage gaps:** None. 97.1% overall, all files above 80%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:** None introduced by this story. The `renderTemplate`/`renderTemplateFile` split is clean and the static file approach is sound.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:** None."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a67b51b482e997339 (use SendMessage with to: 'a67b51b482e997339' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 74095\ntool_uses: 50\nduration_ms: 226161</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f5f7e8e8-6408-46c1-8863-2380ea5a7335","uuid":"8040c420-9627-4b81-b8d0-0e9a3ab2d508","timestamp":"2026-03-25T05:42:17.627Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-3-template-migration-static-files.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nIMPORTANT CONTEXT:\n- The implementation migrated TypeScript template generators to static template files in templates/ with a renderTemplate() function\n- verify-prompt.ts and showboat-template.ts were intentionally NOT migrated (too complex for simple interpolation)\n- 31 template migration tests pass, all other test suites pass\n- Build succeeds\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a67b51b482e997339","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Code Review Summary for Story 15-3: Template Migration -- Static Files**\n\n**Verdict: PASS -- no HIGH or MEDIUM issues found.**\n\nThe implementation is clean and well-structured:\n\n- `renderTemplate()` and `renderTemplateFile()` in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/templates.ts` are correct, well-tested, and handle edge cases (empty vars, unmatched placeholders, multiple occurrences).\n- All migrated templates (`dockerfiles/`, `compose/`, `prompts/`, `docs/`) match their former TypeScript counterparts.\n- Stack providers (`nodejs.ts`, `python.ts`, `rust.ts`) correctly use `renderTemplateFile()` for Dockerfile generation.\n- `docker-compose.ts`, `otel-config.ts`, `readme.ts`, and `ralph-prompt.ts` all correctly delegate to `renderTemplateFile()`.\n- `verify-prompt.ts` and `showboat-template.ts` were intentionally not migrated (complex logic that doesn't reduce to simple `{{VAR}}` interpolation). Correct decision.\n- `package.json` `files` field includes all new template directories for npm distribution.\n- 31 migration-specific tests in `template-migration.test.ts` cover AC1 (directory structure), AC2 (TypeScript generators replaced), and AC3 (output equivalence).\n- All 3777 tests pass. Coverage at 97.1%. All 156 files above 80% per-file floor.\n- Build succeeds.\n\nStory status updated from `review` to `verifying`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:** None.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- `dockerComposeTemplate(_config: DockerComposeConfig)` ignores the `shared` boolean parameter entirely. The function always returns `victoria.yml`. Pre-existing tech debt, not introduced by this story.\n- `otelCollectorConfigWithCors()` injects CORS via regex string manipulation on the YAML output rather than YAML-level manipulation. Fragile if indentation changes in the base template file. Pre-existing, not introduced by this story.\n- Ralph prompt template uses camelCase `{{projectDir}}`, `{{sprintStatusPath}}` while all other templates use `{{SCREAMING_SNAKE}}` convention. Inconsistent but functional since `\\w+` matches both. Introduced by this story but LOW impact.\n- `bmad-patches.ts` uses its own `__dirname`-based path resolution instead of the centralized `getPackageRoot()` from `templates.ts`. Pre-existing.\n\n**Coverage gaps:** None. 97.1% overall, all files above 80%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:** None introduced by this story. The `renderTemplate`/`renderTemplateFile` split is clean and the static file approach is sound.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:** None."}],"totalDurationMs":226161,"totalTokens":74095,"totalToolUseCount":50,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":210,"cache_read_input_tokens":73200,"output_tokens":684,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":210},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
